headline: Agnès Levallois: 'The war in Gaza is political and has no military rationale'
description: In an opinion piece for Le Monde, the vice president of the Institute for Research and Studies on the Mediterranean and the Middle East, analyzes statements by Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, who has announced his intention to take full control of the Gaza Strip.

headline: Maryam, Afghan chef: 'Leaving Afghanistan brought a whirlwind of emotions, not knowing who you are anymore'
description: 'Refugee Recipes' (5/6). Maryam left Afghanistan at the age of 13, crossing 11 countries to reach France. Along the way, in Turkey, she discovered kumpir – a stuffed baked potato – which has since become her lucky dish.

headline: Boko Haram lures young people with no prospects from the Lake Chad area
description: 'Lake Chad's Troubled Waters' (4/4). In Chad's Lac province, 96% of the population is illiterate, and young people have resigned themselves to scraping by with intermittent jobs. This is a boon for the jihadist group, which recruits disadvantaged people by promising them a steady income.

headline: Mojgan Habibi, chef: 'Before, I was afraid of everything. Now, I have found my freedom'
description: 'Refuge Recipes' (4/6). Iranian native Mojgan Habibi is the breakfast chef at Hôtel du Couvent in Nice. Khoresht mast, a dish reserved for special occasions and made with yogurt, spices, honey and meat, brings back memories of her happy youth in Isfahan before her marriage, when she was free to create and sing.

headline: 'We are far too eager to entrust the management of the world to AI instead of recognizing its limits'
description: Media historian Jérôme Bourdon reminds readers that artificial intelligence is part of a long human history, and questions whether this technological revolution is on the verge of becoming a new religion.
